Description:
Large and light in a lifestyle-focused cul-de-sac
Impressive space and natural light take centre stage in this brilliantly updated 3 bedroom apartment quietly set on an oak tree-lined cul-de-sac in a prized South Yarra pocket. Superbly oriented to the north and east in an elegant solid brick block, this spacious first-floor apartment with large covered balcony is an up-styled, light-filled sensation. Position perfect with easy access to the Como Park-Yarra River precinct, Chapel Street, Toorak Village, cinemas, Prahran Market and transport; a fabulous lifestyle is the focus of this attractive home including security intercom and undercover car space on title. Features 3 oversize bedrooms, BIRs, sun-drenched living room, kitchen/meals with stainless-steel appliances, bathroom plus powder room, gas space heating, new carpets and ceiling fans.

Description:
Blue Chip Family Home on 333sqm
This stunning double brick Edwardian family home offers a brilliant opportunity to secure a tightly held property in one of South Yarras most highly regarded blue chip streets. Nestled behind Chapel Street and Toorak Road this well located house comprises secure front garden, entrance hallway, three double bedrooms, large living room with open fire place, spacious kitchen with breakfast area, central bathroom, second living zone or sun room, second bathroom with laundry, separate toilet, deep north/west facing back yard perfect for entertaining, rear access with remote roller door with space to park at least two cars comfortably. Other features include security alarm, ducted gas floor heating, polished floorboards throughout, high ceilings, ornate fire place in bedroom, blue chip location on a large block of land 333sqm (approx). Please note that this lovely home also comes with a set of high end plans which include two storey extension and additional rear garage off rear right of way.

Description:
Designer Style and Sophistication
Completed just months ago, this architecturally striking contemporary residence designed by JAM Architects reveals generous dimensions that are bathed in natural light and showcase cutting edge style and premium finishes. In a coveted location just a short walk to Fawkner Park, the Botanic Gardens, Toorak Rd, Prahran Market, South Yarra station and a range of schools, it delivers immeasurable family lifestyle appeal.
A soaring double height ceiling, white brick feature wall and limed oak floors creates an impactful first impression in the entrance hall which continues through to a sitting room or 4th bedroom overlooking the landscaped forecourt. Bathed in natural light, the expansive open plan living and dining room features a Jetmaster open fire and a state of the art kitchen appointed with Smeg appliances and long stone benches that include a clever home office nook. A sensational extension of the living spaces, the private northwest garden includes a paved entertaining terrace and off street parking via auto gates and a rear lane. Enjoying city views from its west-facing balcony, the beautiful main bedroom features a designer en-suite and built in robes while two additional double bedrooms with built in robes and balcony are accompanied by a stunning bathroom with freestanding bath.
This sanctuary of style also includes an alarm, video intercom, CCTV, under-floor heating, RC/air-conditioning, audio wiring, powder-room, laundry, irrigation, under-ground water tank and ample storage.

Description:
So many possibilities! 8 Art Deco apartments on 1 title: a unique offering
'York House': this landmark Art Deco development (1934 approx) overlooking the Yarra has brilliant possibilities. Offered on a single title for the first time in 40 years, this imposing building is a sound rental investment, with potential for conversion to larger apartments (including a penthouse) or to create one magnificent residence and basement parking (STCA). Presently configured as 8 apartments (7x1BR; 1x2BRs), flamboyantly decorative 'York House' is exclusively positioned with a second frontage to Lawson Grove, close to the Botanical and Darling Gardens, Chapel Street shops, CBD transport and local cafes. In sound condition, this marvellous slice of South Yarra history features decorative ceilings and other classic Deco detail.

Description:
BE THE ENVY OF ALL YOUR FRIENDS!
This stunning 1-bedroom apartment has been architecturally designed and are located in the heart of one of Melbourne's most fashionable neighbourhoods. Chiara & Lucia offers outstanding apartment living in a light filled and liberating space that is sure to take your breath away. Stunning natural colour schemes, fitted with designer stainless steel appliances including dishwasher, stone bench tops, plush carpentry to bedrooms and amazing open plan living that will impress even the most fastidious buyers. Double glazed windows that make it so quiet, you don't even realize you're right in the middle of all the action. Bathroom is featured with large mirror cabinet over vanity and rain shower head. All apartments come with split system for heating and cooling and high security entry/intercom.
Located in the best part of South Yarra with immediate access to amazing retail and dining areas with Chapel Street, Toorak Village, Prahran Markets and The Como all only moments away. Convenient everyday living with a multitude of public transport on offer including trams, buses and South Yarra Station situated only a short 3-minute walk from the building.
Facilities:
• Swimming pool
• Gymnasium
• Sauna and Spa Room
• Communal garden
• Residents lounge and private dining/ function room with separate kitchenette and bathroom
Location:

• 0.35km to The Como
• 0.35km to South Yarra Station
• 0.75km to Village Cinemas Jam Factory
• 1.4km to Hawksburn Station
• 1.7km to Prahran Station
• 4.5km to Melbourne CBD
Please contact Mo Mellak on 0405 083 188 to find out more and to arrange a viewing.

Address: 6/128 Toorak Road West South Yarra VIC 3141
Description:
Significant South Yarra Art Deco Apartment
Beautifully positioned on the top floor of this enchanting circa 1936 Art Deco boutique building of only six designed by esteemed Edward Billson, is this spectacular fully renovated spacious apartment overlooking Fawkner Park, whilst retaining ornate features throughout.
You will be impressed by the entry foyer leading to a generous living room with ornate features and character, high ceilings, open fire place and with adjoining glamourous light filled dining room. The modernised gourmet kitchen has stone bench tops, stainless steel European appliances and ample cupboard space. The flexible floor plan offers a large main bedroom with built in robes, ensuite and study/winter garden area with lush leafy outlooks over Fawkner Park, 2 further bedrooms with central sparkling bathroom.
Other features include hydronic heating, air conditioning, alarm, security intercom, European laundry and single lock up garage.
This outstanding location offers transport on your door step with easy access to the CBD and Arts precinct, opposite 100 acres of pristine parkland, attractive café lifestyle of Domain Road and Toorak Road Village and an easy stroll to the Botanic Gardens.

Description:
Timeless Art Deco with a Prestige Address
Showcasing a prized position directly opposite Darling Gardens and the Yarra River, this magnificent Howard Lawson designed apartment complex is an exquisite expression of both classic Art Deco charm and ambience combined with contemporary comfort. Set amidst a stunning Hollywood-style milieu, the resident facilities boast a pool with grotto and bridge plus a communal rooftop terrace with city views. A showpiece of era grandeur, this one bedroom apartment provides a truly unique entry level into the South Yarra market. Retaining period features such as timber floorboards, high decorative ceilings and leadlight glass, the apartment comprises of a living/dining, separate kitchen with gas cooking, sunny spacious bedroom and a bathroom with washing machine facilities. Toorak Road shops, trams, eateries and South Yarra Station are at one end of the street whilst the Yarra River bike trail is at the other and the Botanic Gardens and popular Lawson Grove Shop are moments away.

Description:
Compelling design, unmatched views.
Breathtaking panoramic views and quality finishes distinguish this superb apartment. Situated in the award winning Central development, this expansive residence offers stylish and convenient living in a lifestyle location. Open plan living connects to a sizeable wraparound balcony offering views of the city and towards the Dandenongs with undercover alfresco dining space to be enjoyed all year round, adjoining a sophisticated kitchen fitted with Miele appliances including dishwasher, gas cooktop and oven. Both bright bedrooms are equipped with built in robes, with the main bedroom also including a sleek ensuite and exquisite views. Description:
Significant South Yarra Art Deco Apartment
Beautifully positioned on the top floor of this enchanting Circa 1936 Art Deco boutique building of only six designed by esteemed Edward Billson, is this spectacular fully renovated spacious apartment overlooking Fawkner Park, whilst retaining ornate features throughout.
You will be impressed by the entry foyer leading to a generous living room with ornate features and character, high ceilings, open fire place and with adjoining glamourous light filled dining room. The modernised gourmet kitchen has stone bench tops, stainless steel European appliances and ample cupboards space. The flexible floor plan offers a large main bedroom with built in robes, en-suite and study/winter garden area with lush leafy outlooks over Fawkner Park, 2 further bedrooms with central sparkling bathroom.
Other features include hydronic heating, air conditioning, alarm, security intercom, European laundry and single lock up garage.
This outstanding location offers transport on your door step with easy access to the CBD and Arts precinct, opposite 100 acres of pristine parkland, attractive cafe lifestyle of Domain Road and Toorak Road Village and an easy stroll to the Botanic Gardens.

Description:
Glamorous Lifestyle Living with Amazing Views To Port Phillip Bay
Luxury, exclusivity and spectacular bay views wrapping around to far reaching northern views are a rare privilege in any setting, yet this remarkable elevated 16th floor apartment boasts just this in Melbournes most iconic fashion and lifestyle address! Positioned metres from cosmopolitan Toorak Road in the luxurious Ella Apartments, a cleverly customised corner layout enjoys glamorous interiors wrapped in a breathtaking floor to ceiling panorama that sweeps up Toorak Road to Port Phillip Bay and across to the north past Melbourne High School and the Yarra River. A glass-wrapped north and west facing living and dining zone with a chic bio ethanol fireplace opens to a glass framed balcony and integrates a sleek stone kitchen with smoked glass splashback and Miele appliances including an integrated dishwasher. Two generous fitted bedrooms include the main bedroom with a superb ensuite with high end finishes and matching main bathroom with hidden laundry. Oak flooring, reverse-cycle air conditioning, lift access from a glamorous hotel style foyer, secure basement parking, storage cage and low body corporate fees enhance a truly unique lifestyle or investment opportunity with every Chapel Street delight, Yarra bike and walking trails, Toorak Road restaurants trams, South Yarra station and so much more at the doorstep.

"Domain Park" - Iconic Location, Impressive Views
Commanding spectacular views over the Botanic Gardens to the city skyline, the MCG and AAMI Park from the 11th floor of the celebrated Robin Boyd designed building, this immaculately presented apartment delivers exceptional lock up and leave lifestyle appeal meters from the restaurants and shops in the Domain Precinct, Toorak Rd, trams and schools.

Description:
Stunning Style Bathed In Northern Light
The coming together of everything that is good about life in South Yarra, this executive town residence dishes up the ultimate low maintenance lifestyle from its tree-lined boulevard metres to renowned eateries, boutiques, transport and parks. Secure, secluded and stylish, the home forms part of the 'Abingdon' group of architect-designed residences.
Finished with class and a nod towards French Provincial elegance, the main level showcases gorgeous travertine floors which flow throughout the entertaining zone out to the landscaped alfresco patio. Indoors offers space for relaxing beside the fireplace or hosting family and friends, the generous stone kitchen with premium Siemens appliances providing the perfect space for all your gourmet endeavours.
Comprising three spacious bedrooms including an attractive ensuite master, this first-class abode also features a luxe full bathroom, lower level powder room and laundry/pantry area that flows easily from the designer kitchen. Plantation shutters and pretty sheers also star, zoned heating and cooling ensure comfort, whilst finalising the premium offering are secure basement parking for two cars, plus considerable storage with private internal access.

UNBEATABLE LIFESTYLE LOCATION

- Secure entrance

Description:
Living The Good Life At Lovely Lilli
Backed by the illustrious design hallmarks of Elenberg Fraser and Hecker Guthrie, the Lilli development pays homage to Melbournes laneway culture, with a pedestrian thoroughfare creating a retail precinct linking Chapel Street to South Yarra station. Enjoy proximity to Toorak Road, Chapel Street, Yarra River bike trails and myriad retail, dining, cafe and transport options.
A layout conceived with convenience and style define this 12th floor apartment, notable for sleek, contemporary finishes and custom joinery. Ushering into an entry with fully tiled bathroom offering oversized shower, separate euro laundry and luxury bedroom including heating and BIRs, the living zone opens out to a stunning Miele equipped stone-topped kitchen with integrated dish drawer and pristine white suspended cabinetry. A well-lit lounge has split-system heating/cooling and extends out to a covered balcony complete with built-in BBQ. Along with a basement car space, intercom entrance and a secure, yet funkily impressive lobby, this immaculate property creates the ideal first home, handy pied-à-terre or informed investment decision and wont last long!
